# .cursorule for Viral Together UI (Next.js 14)

# Project Overview
This is a Next.js 14 UI application for the Viral Together influencer marketing platform.
It connects to the API repository at ../viral-together and provides a modern web interface.

# Tech Stack
- Next.js 14 with App Router
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- React Hook Form
- Axios for API calls
- Lucide React for icons

# Development Commands
dev: npm run dev
build: npm run build
start: npm run start
lint: npm run lint
type-check: npm run type-check

# Environment Variables
API_URL: http://localhost:8000 (points to the viral-together API)
NODE_ENV: development

# Key Directories
- src/app: Next.js 14 App Router pages
- src/components: Reusable React components
- src/lib: Utility functions and API client
- src/types: TypeScript type definitions
- src/hooks: Custom React hooks

# API Integration
The app integrates with the viral-together API for:
- Authentication (JWT tokens)
- Influencer management
- Rate card management
- Subscription handling
- Search and analytics

# Specify the test command for running tests
test: npm run test

# Specify any ignored files or directories
ignore:
  - node_modules
  - .next
  - .git
  - .env.local  # Ignore local environment variables